==English==
===Etymology===
From Middle English < Latin ''[[epicoenus]]'' < Greek [[επίκοινος]] ('common').

===Adjective===
'''epicene'''

#Having the [[characteristic]]s of both [[male]] and [[female]].
#[[Effeminate]] or [[unmanly]].
#{{linguistics}} Having only one form of the [[noun]] for both the male and the female.

